  '41d6f2e7-3ae4-43b7-abb6-38e3bbff6f42',
  '168cee73-f1ba-486c-a41e-3d356b828b37',
  $$Explain the difference between Angular RouterModule.forRoot and forChild$$,
  $$forRoot() registers the Router service and should be called exactly once in the root AppModule (or bootstrapApplication). It owns the router-outlet and handles navigation globally. forChild() adds routes to the existing router without re-creating the service — used in feature modules to lazy-load routes.$$,
