  '34d4d7de-8ada-4227-9909-92124adbffbc',
  '168cee73-f1ba-486c-a41e-3d356b828b37',
  $$What is the React reconciliation algorithm and how does it decide what to re-render?$$,
  $$React's reconciler (Fiber) diffs the new virtual DOM tree against the previous one. It uses two heuristics: (1) Elements of different types produce completely different trees — the old subtree is unmounted. (2) Elements with the same type are updated in place. The key prop is the escape hatch: changing a key forces React to unmount and remount the element even if the type is the same.$$,
