  '168cee73-f1ba-486c-a41e-3d356b828b37',
  $$Explain useCallback and useMemo — when should you actually use them?$$,
  $$useMemo caches a computed value between renders; useCallback caches a function reference. Both only matter when the memoized value is passed to a child wrapped in React.memo, or is a dependency of another hook. Premature memoization adds overhead (cache comparison + closure allocation) for no benefit. Profile first, then memoize.$$,
